  "texts": [
    "The exact analytical framework each gradient-based method employs depends on the set of model parameters considered (Hammoudeh & Lowd, 2022).",
    "Static, gradient-based methods-discussed first-estimate the effect of retraining by studying gradients w.r.t.",
    "final model parameters (T).",
    "Obviously, a single set of model parameters provide limited insight into the entire optimization landscape, meaning static methods generally must make stronger assumptions.",
    "In contrast, dynamic, gradient-based influence estimators reconstruct the training data's influence by studying model parameters throughout training, e.g., (0), …, (T)."
